Global warming is predicted to exacerbate droughts and decrease Colorado River flows, impacting water supplies for Western states.
The river is crucial for Metropolitan, Southern California's main water source, with 30% of deliveries coming from the Colorado.
Agricultural water is highlighted as vital for urban use.
Uncertainty exists regarding climate change effects on precipitation.
States are collaborating to manage current drought conditions, with reservoirs at half capacity.
Water scarcity poses a significant challenge, with the US and Europe better equipped than African nations.
Efforts to revive the Colorado River delta are ongoing, with various water management strategies in place.
